####### FLY directory structure

-- top dir
   For most pages, two files, e.g.
   edit_member_content.php (has the layout of the page/fields)
   edit_member.php (invoked for actions on the page)

   .gitignore - crucial for missing secure files

-- backups
   not in git
   db backups and web pages

-- bin
   convenience scripts
   needs fix for passwords: dumpDBs.sh (removed from git)

-- css
   style sheets

-- etc
   used for install, generic db
   alter scripts to update DB

-- hfl
   contains upload .igc files for hi far long competition

-- images
   graphics used

-- js
   javascript libs used

-- lib
   IGC.php - function to read .igc flight track
   common.inc - general utility functions used in php code
   config.inc - general layout/configuration info (no security stuff)
   database.inc - check/open connection to DB
   db_funcs.inc - utility DB functions
   fly_funcs.inc - utility functions specific to fly
   footer.inc - end of every page, contains code to display session variables
                based on DebugLevel
   header.inc - start of every page, maintains session, remember user.
   hfl.inc - defines user for high/far/log
   hostname.inc - ?
   mode.inc - contains secure info, passwords, emails (not in git)
   sess_funcs.inc - login session functions
   states.php - state abbrev. ?

-- photos
   not in git
   glider and member photos (secure)
  

